race.comment: PRAISE YOU (7) was a touch disappointing last time out but the four placings prior were full of merit. Gets some weight off from the low draw and can improve enough to play a prominent role. KING MAL (1) was too bad to be true at the latest outing but the two placings to start the career were good enough for a race like this. Can bounce right back. ELROND (4) has placed two from two around this circuit and gets plenty of weight relief with the 3kg claim. One for the exotics players. ORMOND ROAD (12) next in line while fresh at a nice each way quote. Don't mind the look of PARAT SIBIFORTUNAM (2) at career start two either after he stuck on fairly for a placing on debut.
